Internally this op uses a single per-graph scratch buffer, which means that it will block if multiple versions are being run in parallel. This is because this operator is primarily an optimization to minimize memory usage.

In general, the tf.data service is expected to live for the duration of a single training job. To use the tf.data service with multiple training jobs, make sure to use different job names to avoid conflicts. trans-unit.source: MobileNets support any input size greater than 32 x 32, with larger image sizes offering better performance. By altering the image size and alpha parameter, all 16 models from the paper can be built, with ImageNet weights provided.
